          "value": "<div class=\"rd__b  rd__b--3\"><p>The ophio fungus focuses its spores on up to three creatures it can see within 30 feet of it. Each creature must make a [[/save ability=constitution dc=15]] saving throw. On a failure, a creature takes 14 ([[/damage 4d6 type=poison]]) damage and, if it is a humanoid, it becomes infected with @disease[ophio spores|ToB2]. On a success, a creature takes half the damage and isn't infected with spores. A creature that doesn't need to breathe automatically succeeds on this saving throw. A creature that does need to breathe can still be affected, even if it holds its breath.</p><div class=\"rd__spc-inline-post\"></div></div>",
